<table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td class="text-block" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="main-content" >
<p style="color: #666666; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-069e0cb0-8116-5510-7ce1-bdb2f26143c1"> </span></p>
<p style="color: #666666; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;" dir="ltr"><span>To All Pivotal Employees,</span><br /><br /><span><span id="docs-internal-guid-559a77a8-02e3-b959-57b0-44e29fe01543"><span><span>One of Pivotal&rsquo;s     
 responsibilities to our clients and to ourselves is to have a balanced, reasonable, and kind approach to security.
      The IT team&rsquo;s goal is to keep the information of our company and our clients&rsquo; companies secure, while keeping the overhead and inconvenience for employees to a minimum.
      To this end, we originally rolled out a set of controls for phones and tablets that access Pivotal data.
      After gathering feedback from many of you, we&rsquo;ve arrived at an updated policy and management plan for personal devices.</span><br /><br /><span><strong>Options for accessing Pivotal accounts on your personal device:</strong></span></span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Directly connect your device to Google Services through apps (e.g.
      Gmail, Google Drive) or system settings.*Requires installing an MDM profile on your device*</li>
<li>Use IMAP, CalDAV, CardDAV, Google application-specific passwords, and set a passcode lock on your device.</li>
<li>Use a web client or the Okta Mobile app.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="ltr"><span id="docs-internal-guid-559a77a8-02e3-b959-57b0-44e29fe01543"><span style="color: #666666; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;"><strong>Details:</strong></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;">These controls will apply to iOS as well as Android</span></li>
<li><span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;">When we first switched to pivotal.io, Google&rsquo;s Mobile Device Management (MDM) controls only worked on Android devices.
      They now work on iOS devices as well.
      By June 1, 2015, we will update these controls so that they apply to both Android and iOS devices.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: #666666; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;"><strong>Specifically:</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>On iOS if you download the Gmail, Google Drive, or other Google apps and log in with your pivotal.io account, or connect to your pivotal.io account through iOS system  settings, it will prompt you to put MDM controls on your phone or tablet.</li>
<li>Pivotal will only use a small subset of these controls.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span>These MDM controls will only do four things:&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Require you to set a device passcode</li>
<li>Require you to change the passcode every 365 days</li>
<li>Encrypt your device&rsquo;s data with that passcode</li>
<li>Allow Pivotal IT to delete all data from your MDM-managed device</li>
</ol>
<p>We don&rsquo;t want that last one.
    Unfortunately, we can&rsquo;t turn it off.
    Since we can&rsquo;t deactivate it, Pivotal promises to never remote wipe a personal device without a written request from the device&rsquo;s owner.
    We have limited this ability to just a handful of senior IT employees - the same group that already has the &ldquo;keys to the kingdom&rdquo;.
    It&rsquo;s documented in our <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://docs.google.com/a/pivotal.io/document/d/1HYGdNqK6LjbgawGOSSDSMm1D6lBSzRzo3NMW4tRgLHE)">official policy</a>.&nbsp;<br /><br /><span>These controls will not allow Pivotal the ability to access the data 
on   your phone, track your location, or do anything  other than the four things mentioned above.</span><br /><br /><span><strong>We have other options for folks who wish to avoid these controls:</strong><br /><br />If you aren&rsquo;t comfortable having these MDM controls on your personal device, 
you  are welcome to  set a passcode manually and access your Pivotal  data via IMAP, CardDAV, and CalDAV.<br /><br />This method is somewhat more technical, and you won&rsquo;t be able to access all features.
    However, it will let you access the majority of your Pivotal data without MDM controls.
    If you&rsquo;d like a hand setting this up, please email us:&nbsp;<a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="mailto:ask@pivotal.io">ask@pivotal.io</a>&nbsp;or visit the IT <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" 
href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/pivotal-it/gmail/application-specific-passwords-for-native-applications">wiki</a> for instructions.&nbsp;<br /><br />You can also access your Pivotal data through your phone&rsquo;s web browser or the Okta Mobile app, neither of which require MDM   
controls.<br /><br /><strong>You will need a unique password for each native app.</strong><br /><br />This only applies to you if you have native  apps on your phone or desktop that require your pivotal.io Google Apps password.
    For instance, if you use Exchange, Apple Mail, Thunderbird, or similar applications.
    In that case, you will need to set up a custom password for each app of this type you use.
    If you&rsquo;d like a hand, please reach out to us:&nbsp;<a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="mailto:ask@pivotal.io">ask@pivotal.io</a>.<br /><br />Thanks for your attention and understanding.<br /><br />We&rsquo;re using MDM controls because it&rsquo;s the responsible thing 
 to  do for our  clients&rsquo;, our customers&rsquo;, and our data.
    We also want you to have an excellent experience working at Pivotal.
    We&rsquo;ve added an <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/pivotal-it/mobile-devices/bring-your-own-device-byod-and-opting-in-to-device-management">FAQ page</a> to the IT wiki, and we&rsquo;ll be holding a series of Q&amp;A sessions so 
you   can ask questions directly.
    If you&rsquo;d like to reach out ahead of those sessions, please email&nbsp;<a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="mailto:ask@pivotal.io">ask@pivotal.io</a>.<br /><br /></span>Best,<br />Drew</p>
